"{\"uid\": \"tnonline.com-20240729-allentown-bishop-criticizes-opening-ceremony-of-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Allentown Bishop Alfred A. Schlert publicly criticized the opening ceremony of the 2024 Paris Olympics in a letter released Sunday, condemning a performance he described as a \\\"horrendous depiction of the Last Supper.\\\"\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 219, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Allentown Bishop Alfred A. Schlert\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 34}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 55, \"to\": 75}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 79, \"to\": 102}, {\"ngram\": \"a letter\", \"from\": 106, \"to\": 114}, {\"ngram\": \"a performance\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 156}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"horrendous depiction\", \"from\": 173, \"to\": 196}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 200, \"to\": 215}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In his letter, Schlert expressed his dismay over the portrayal of a drag queen as Jesus and transvestite apostles, calling it a sacrilegious mockery of the Christian faith.\", \"from\": 221, \"to\": 393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 303, \"end\": 308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.999999896947207, \"rank\": 1.0305267510104864e-07, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 377, \"end\": 386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999756423184623, \"rank\": 2.435827475270085e-05, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his letter\", \"from\": 224, \"to\": 234}, {\"ngram\": \"Schlert\", \"from\": 236, \"to\": 243}, {\"ngram\": \"his dismay\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 264}, {\"ngram\": \"the portrayal\", \"from\": 270, \"to\": 283}, {\"ngram\": \"a drag queen\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 299}, {\"ngram\": \"transvestite apostles\", \"from\": 313, \"to\": 334}, {\"ngram\": \"a sacrilegious mockery\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 369}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With one billion people watching, a horrendous depiction of the Last Supper, complete with a monstrous drag queen 'Jesus' and transvestite 'apostles,' was offered by the French Olympic organizers as their disdain and ridicule of the Christian faith,\\\" Schlert wrote.\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.999999896947207, \"rank\": 1.0305267510104864e-07, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 566, \"end\": 572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.7069598880928705, \"rank\": 0.24609425856191688, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 629, \"end\": 638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999756423184623, \"rank\": 2.435827475270085e-05, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one billion people\", \"from\": 401, \"to\": 419}, {\"ngram\": \"a horrendous depiction\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 452}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 471}, {\"ngram\": \"transvestite 'apostles\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 544}, {\"ngram\": \"their disdain\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 608}, {\"ngram\": \"ridicule\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 621}, {\"ngram\": \"Schlert\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He emphasized the historical significance of France as the \\\"Eldest Daughter of the Church\\\" and lamented the mockery occurring in a country with deep Catholic roots.\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 708, \"end\": 714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.7288151932990352, \"rank\": 0.34794763373203513, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 812, \"end\": 820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999943237944197, \"rank\": 5.596174246445142e-06, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the historical significance\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 704}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"Eldest Daughter\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 738}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 752}, {\"ngram\": \"the mockery\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"a country\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 801}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Schlert's statement came shortly after his return from the 10th National Eucharistic Congress in Indianapolis, where he and others from the Diocese participated in a Eucharistic Procession and a concluding Holy Mass.\", \"from\": 829, \"to\": 1045, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 902, \"end\": 922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharistic_congress\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.4544079795057683e-13, \"text\": \"Eucharistic Congress\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharistic_congress\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharistic_congress\"}, {\"begin\": 926, \"end\": 938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"score\": 0.9999729286693306, \"rank\": 2.60012129502432e-05, \"text\": \"Indianapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Schlert's statement\", \"from\": 829, \"to\": 848}, {\"ngram\": \"his return\", \"from\": 868, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"the Diocese\", \"from\": 965, \"to\": 976}, {\"ngram\": \"a Eucharistic Procession\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1017}, {\"ngram\": \"a concluding Holy Mass.\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The next day, last Sunday, the Eucharistic Congress concluded with a splendid Holy Mass, full of the vigor of the entire Church.\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1079, \"end\": 1099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharistic_congress\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.4544079795057683e-13, \"text\": \"Eucharistic Congress\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharistic_congress\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharistic_congress\"}, {\"begin\": 1126, \"end\": 1135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mass_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.32502877938942e-17, \"text\": \"Holy Mass\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mass_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mass_in_the_Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the vigor\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1154}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire Church\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1175}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Our Lord was truly present in those days,\\\" he said, contrasting the spiritual experience of the Congress with the Olympics' opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1273, \"end\": 1281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\", \"score\": 0.9999518556258493, \"rank\": 3.630675936782004e-05, \"text\": \"Congress\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Our Lord\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1185}, {\"ngram\": \"those days\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1217}, {\"ngram\": \"the spiritual experience\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics' opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1287, \"to\": 1317}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The performance in Paris sparked a debate among viewers with some seeing it as a bold artistic statement while others, like Schlert, viewed it as deeply offensive.\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1483, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999997957441091, \"rank\": 2.0425592828813242e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The performance\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1335}, {\"ngram\": \"a debate\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1361}, {\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1375}, {\"ngram\": \"a bold artistic statement\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1424}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1437}, {\"ngram\": \"Schlert\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1451}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Defenders of the ceremony argue that it was intended to challenge traditional representations and provoke thought about inclusivity and acceptance in modern society.\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1649, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Defenders\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1493}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1509}, {\"ngram\": \"traditional representations\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1577}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusivity\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1615}, {\"ngram\": \"acceptance\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"modern society\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1648}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They suggested the performance was not meant to mock, but rather to re-imagine and bring attention to contemporary issues through a familiar narrative.\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1801, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1680}, {\"ngram\": \"attention\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1748}, {\"ngram\": \"contemporary issues\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1771}, {\"ngram\": \"a familiar narrative\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1800}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers released a statement over the weekend indicating the scene was not portraying the Last Supper, but instead depicting the Greek god Dionysus and an ancient festival meant to honor him.\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1935, \"end\": 1940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.4413306829332979, \"rank\": 0.8306980529166041, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1945, \"end\": 1953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8414941465142303e-15, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1813}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1834}, {\"ngram\": \"the weekend\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1851}, {\"ngram\": \"the scene\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1872}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1907}, {\"ngram\": \"an ancient festival\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 1977}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Clearly there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group,\\\" Paris 2024 spokesperson Anne Descamps said in a daily press briefing.\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2081, \"end\": 2091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999972024548265, \"rank\": 2.7975530473931137e-06, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2110, \"end\": 2118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an intention\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2036}, {\"ngram\": \"any religious group\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2078}, {\"ngram\": \"a daily press briefing\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2149}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"On the contrary, I think Thomas Jolly, we really did try to celebrate community tolerance.\", \"from\": 2151, \"to\": 2242, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the contrary\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2167}, {\"ngram\": \"community tolerance\", \"from\": 2222, \"to\": 2241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Looking at the result of the polls that we shared, we believe that this ambition was achieved.\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2337, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the result\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2264}, {\"ngram\": \"the polls\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"this ambition\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If people have taken any offense, we are, of course, really, really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 2338, \"to\": 2413, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2347}, {\"ngram\": \"any offense\", \"from\": 2359, \"to\": 2370}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2389}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Bishop Schlert said he saw the performance as part of a broader trend of secularization and marginalization of the Church.\", \"from\": 2415, \"to\": 2546, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2424, \"end\": 2430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"score\": 0.999521230981044, \"rank\": 0.0004789982544479133, \"text\": \"Bishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2466}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2470, \"to\": 2474}, {\"ngram\": \"a broader trend\", \"from\": 2478, \"to\": 2493}, {\"ngram\": \"secularization\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2511}, {\"ngram\": \"marginalization\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2531}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2545}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"While this scandal occurred in France, given the increasing secularization and marginalization of the Church in our own Country, it could also happen here,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2580, \"end\": 2586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.7288151932990352, \"rank\": 0.34794763373203513, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this scandal\", \"from\": 2555, \"to\": 2567}, {\"ngram\": \"the increasing secularization\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2623}, {\"ngram\": \"marginalization\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2643}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2657}, {\"ngram\": \"our own Country\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2676}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He called on the faithful to \\\"recommit to public witness and reverence of the Holy Eucharist, pledging efforts to become Eucharistic missionaries and to undertake acts of reparation and penance.\\\"\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2794, \"end\": 2808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2695176784472078e-16, \"text\": \"Holy Eucharist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"public witness\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2772}, {\"ngram\": \"reverence\", \"from\": 2777, \"to\": 2786}, {\"ngram\": \"efforts\", \"from\": 2819, \"to\": 2826}, {\"ngram\": \"Eucharistic missionaries\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 2861}, {\"ngram\": \"acts\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 2883}, {\"ngram\": \"reparation\", \"from\": 2887, \"to\": 2897}, {\"ngram\": \"penance\", \"from\": 2902, \"to\": 2909}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The enemy wastes no time in trying to shock and discourage us, but our weapon is the Holy Eucharist, the power of which will never be defeated,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 3067, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2999, \"end\": 3013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2695176784472078e-16, \"text\": \"Holy Eucharist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The enemy\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 2923}, {\"ngram\": \"no time\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 2938}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2973, \"to\": 2975}, {\"ngram\": \"our weapon\", \"from\": 2981, \"to\": 2991}, {\"ngram\": \"the power\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3024}]}]}"